Roots \((-1, 1, 6)\): - Sum: \(-1 + 1 + 6 = 6\) �� \(a = -6\) - Product pairs: \((-1)(1) + (-1)(6) + (1)(6) = -1 - 6 + 6 = -1\) �� \(b = -1\) - Pair: \((-6, -1)\) 3. Roots \((-1, 2, 3)\): - Sum: \(-1 + 2 + 3 = 4\) �� \(a = -4\) - Product pairs: \((-1)(2) + (-1)(3) + (2)(3) = -2 - 3 + 6 = 1\) �� \(b = 1\) - Pair: \((-4, 1)\) 4. Roots \((1, 2, -3)\): - Sum: \(1 + 2 + (-3) = 0\) �� \(a = 0\) - Product pairs: \(1 \cdot 2 + 1 \cdot (-3) + 2 \cdot (-3) = 2 - 3 - 6 = -7\) �� \(b = -7\) - Pair: \((0, -7)\) 5. Roots \((1, 3, -2)\): - Sum: \(1 + 3 + (-2) = 2\) �� \(a = -2\) - Product pairs: \(1 \cdot 3 + 1 \cdot (-2) + 3 \cdot (-2) = 3 - 2 - 6 = -5\) �� \(b = -5\) - Pair: \((-2, -5)\) Each set of roots results in a distinct ordered pair \((a, b)\). Therefore, the number of ordered pairs \((a, b)\) is \(\boxed{5}\).
